  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>Qpop is a customer-facing application designed to enhance interaction and engagement at the point of sale through a dedicated touchscreen interface. Always facing the customer, Qpop allows for seamless interaction during the sales process by:</p><ul><li><p>Displaying in-store advertisements and promotions</p></li><li><p>Showing real-time ticket details for customer review</p></li><li><p>Presenting electronic forms and waivers for acknowledgment</p></li><li><p>Capturing electronic signatures for payments via integrated devices</p></li></ul><p>Once you add a Qpop Companion to your RepairQ location, you must pair the device to a terminal. A companion can be paired with multiple terminals at the same time.</p><p><strong>Note: </strong>Qpop Companions are intended to run as Always-On status for both the screen and internet connection. Most tablets will disconnect from Wi-Fi when the screen times out or goes into sleep mode. When running Qpop, ensure your tablet is plugged in and screen timeout and auto-sleep settings have been turned off. We also recommend enabling Kiosk Mode on your tablet first to ensure that customers cannot navigate away from the Qpop browser page.</p><h3 id=\"PairaQpop\u2122Companion-PreviousStep\">Previous Step</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1937014846/Create+a+Qpop+Companion\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1937014846\" data-linked-resource-version=\"13\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Create a Qpop\u2122 Companion</a></p></li></ul><h3 id=\"PairaQpop\u2122Companion-OptionalFeaturesandAdditionalResources\">Optional Features and Additional Resources</h3><ul><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936949331/Send+Custom+Forms+to+Your+Qpop+Companion+Device\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936949331\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Send Custom Forms to Qpop\u2122 Companion</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936359503/Capture+Integrated+Payment+Signatures+on+a+Qpop+Companion\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936359503\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Capture Integrated Payment Signatures on a Qpop\u2122 Companion</a> </p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936588867/Qpop+Companion+-+Enable+Kiosk+Mode+on+iOS\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936588867\" data-linked-resource-version=\"9\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Qpop\u2122 Companion - Kiosk Mode on iOS</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936523314/Qpop+Companion+-+Enable+Kiosk+Mode+on+Android\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936523314\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Qpop\u2122 Companion - Kiosk Mode on Android</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1936654410/Qpop+Companion+Troubleshooting\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1936654410\" data-linked-resource-version=\"8\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Qpop\u2122 Companion Troubleshooting</a></p></li><li><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1937047567/Qpop+Companion+Resources+with+Video\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1937047567\" data-linked-resource-version=\"13\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Qpop\u2122 Companion Resources</a> </p></li></ul><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936490516/image-20230608-175650.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"PairaQpop\u2122Companion-PairQpopWithYourTerminal\">Pair Qpop With Your Terminal</h2><h3 id=\"PairaQpop\u2122Companion-OnYourComputer/Terminal\">On Your Computer/Terminal</h3><p>Navigate to your RepairQ URL and log in to your location. On the Navigation Bar, click the <strong>Location Shortname</strong> <strong>dropdown</strong>. From the list of options, click\u00a0<strong>Pair Qpop</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936490516/image-20230608-175657.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>On the Qpop Companion pop-up, select which companion you would like to use from the dropdown list. Once you have made your selection, click <strong>Pair</strong>. The pop-up will display generate a code. Keep this screen open while you log into your Qpop tablet.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936490516/image-20230608-175703.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936490516/image-20230608-175708.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"PairaQpop\u2122Companion-OnYourQpopCompanionDevice\">On Your Qpop Companion Device</h3><p>Navigate to your RepairQ URL and log in to your location. Under the Get Started section of the dashboard, click <strong>Launch Qpop</strong>. You will be directed to the <strong>Welcome to Qpop</strong> page. Enter the code that was generated by RepairQ on your computer and tap <strong>Pair</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936490516/image-20230608-175714.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" alt=\"Pairing 7.5.png\" width=\"463\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936490516/Pairing%207.5.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><h3 id=\"PairaQpop\u2122Companion-PairingConfirmation\">Pairing Confirmation</h3><p>When paired, your computer will display an image, showing that the companion has paired successfully and your Companion will show the Idle Screen.</p><p><strong>Note:\u00a0</strong>If the pairing was unsuccessful or you need to generate a new pairing code, you can click <strong>Get New Code</strong> on the popup on your computer.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936490516/image-20230608-175725.png?api=v2\"></span><h2 id=\"PairaQpop\u2122Companion-Optional:AddaQpopCompanionLinktoYourHomeScreen\">Optional: Add a Qpop Companion Link to Your Home Screen</h2><h3 id=\"PairaQpop\u2122Companion-iPadOS\">iPadOS</h3><p>When viewing the idle screen on your browser, tap <strong>Share</strong> on the toolbar. Then, tap <strong>Add to Home Screen</strong>. Name your link something that is easy to identify, then tap <strong>Add</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936490516/image-20230608-175740.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936490516/image-20230608-175746.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>Your home screen will now have a link directly to your Qpop Companion page.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936490516/image-20230608-175752.png?api=v2\"></span><h3 id=\"PairaQpop\u2122Companion-Android\">Android</h3><p>When viewing the idle screen on your browser, tap <strong>Options </strong>on your toolbar. On the list of options, tap <strong>Add to Home Screen</strong>. Name your link something that is easy to identify, then tap <strong>Add</strong>.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936490516/image-20230608-175757.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936490516/image-20230608-175802.png?api=v2\"></span><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"519\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936490516/image-20230608-175806.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p>Your home screen will now have a link to your Qpop Companion page.</p><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper confluence-embedded-manual-size\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image confluence-content-image-border image-center\" width=\"507\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1936490516/image-20230608-175813.png?api=v2\"></span><p /><p /><p>START 1.21.X</p>",
